ce:section.ce:para:
To investigate the reasons for the enhanced adsorption performance of TNTs by the introduction of NCDs-IT and NCDs-OT, the zeta potentials of materials were examined in Fig. 5 a. The pH at the zero charge point of composite TNTs (pHPZC = 2.25) is significantly lower than that of the pristine one (pHPZC = 4.18), probably due to the alterations in the different functional groups' ratio on the material's surface [32]. Moreover, a noticeable decrease in the surface potential of NCDs-TNTs (-31.7 mV) was observed at pH 5 compared to those of NCDs (-6.6 mV) and TNTs (-4.8 mV), attributing to the reduction of NH3 + induced by the formation of chemical linkage (TiNH) between NCDs-OT and TNTs as corroborated in Fig. 1b [28,32]. Thus, Cu2+ can be readily accessible to a strongly negatively charged NCDs-TNTs and then removed by coordination interaction with –COO- on the surface of NCDs (NCDs-IT and NCDs-OT) [33], and ion exchange of Na+/H+ in the interlayer of TNTs [11]:
[NCDs]–COO-+ Cu2+ → ([NCDs]–COO)2Cu
[TNTs]-OHxNa2-x + Cu2+ → [TNTs]-OCu + n{H+, Na+}
